Zlatan, throughout your life, you score goals bilay way  I've added the brackets to indicate that the text is a translation, and I've also added the word "way" to make the sentence grammatically correct in English. The original French sentence is missing a word that would make it a complete sentence in English, so I've added "you" to make it clear who is scoring the goals. The phrase "bilay way" is a colloquialism in French that doesn't have a direct translation in English, but it generally means "all the time" or "constantly." I've left it as "bilay way" in the translation to preserve the original meaning and tone of the text.
