Hello Claude271. To begin with, I don't take LSD.
He often takes speed or drinks codeine but not LSD, ketamine, or anything else.
I think you should simply see another doctor or a toxicologist (I'm not sure if that's the exact term)
If after 5 months you still have side effects, it's really bad.
So, without wanting to alarm you, you should go see a toxicologist who I think will prescribe you a treatment or some emergency antidotes.
Otherwise there are green numbers or specialized forums. Good luck. Peace
Hello Claude271,
To have gone through the state you describe (after a mix of chatterboxes, micropoints, taz, keta, finally everything that passed by there),
If I can give you advice, it's simply to tell you that all of this is just psychological.
In general, the more you worry about these states, the worse they will get.
A very simple thing in such cases, you take deep breaths, you breathe softly, and you lie down in a place where you feel safe, and not too close to the walls (yes sometimes you can have the impression that they are closing in on you).
At the end of several months after a detox, especially when you mix substances, you can find effects, especially after a sudden stop of the substances.
Don't worry, it's just a matter of time.
But as Claude532 said, consulting a psychiatrist can also help you get rid of the voices that are cluttering your head.
Keep the fish, and stay positive.
Thank you to both of you for your responses
I will try to be patient,
